---
// Chooser page — served at /mockups/ (Astro page, so the directory URL resolves)
---
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
<title>Caterlord — Design Refresh · 6 Options</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Space+Grotesk:wght@600;700&family=Inter:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
</head>
<body>
<style is:global>
  :root{--ink:#0f172a;--soft:#5b6672;--line:#e6ecf2;--blue:#00b0fa;--bg:#fff;--warm:#fbf6ea}
  *{box-sizing:border-box}
  body{margin:0;font-family:"Inter",system-ui,sans-serif;color:var(--ink);background:var(--bg)}
  .wrap{max-width:1140px;margin:0 auto;padding:clamp(28px,6vw,56px) clamp(20px,5vw,40px)}
  h1{font-family:"Space Grotesk",sans-serif;font-size:clamp(1.7rem,3.6vw,2.6rem);margin:0 0 6px;letter-spacing:-.02em}
  .lede{color:var(--soft);max-width:62ch;margin:0 0 14px}
  .group{font-family:"Space Grotesk",sans-serif;font-size:.8rem;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--soft);margin:30px 0 14px}
  .grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:16px}
  .card{display:block;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:16px;overflow:hidden;text-decoration:none;color:var(--ink);transition:transform .12s,box-shadow .2s,border-color .2s}
  .card:hover{transform:translateY(-4px);box-shadow:0 18px 40px rgba(15,40,70,.1);border-color:var(--blue)}
  .card .thumb{aspect-ratio:5/3;display:grid;place-items:center;font-family:"Space Grotesk",sans-serif;font-weight:700;font-size:2.6rem}
  .card .b{padding:16px 18px 20px}
  .card .tag{font-size:.72rem;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--soft);font-weight:600}
  .card h2{font-family:"Space Grotesk",sans-serif;font-size:1.22rem;margin:5px 0 7px}
  .card p{color:var(--soft);font-size:.86rem;margin:0;line-height:1.45}
  .a .thumb{background:#fbf8f2;color:#1a1714}
  .b .thumb{background:#e6f7fe;color:#0095d6}
  .c .thumb{background:radial-gradient(circle at 30% 30%,#00b0fa,#070b16);color:#fff}
  .d .thumb{background:var(--warm);color:#1b1b1b;border-bottom:1px dashed #c9bfa6;font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace}
  .e .thumb{background:#0a0a0a;color:#fff;font-family:Anton,sans-serif;letter-spacing:.02em}
  .e .thumb span{color:#0066ff}
  .f .thumb{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#b5482e,#3c5240);color:#fff;font-family:Georgia,serif;font-style:normal}
  .note{margin-top:30px;padding:16px 18px;background:#f5f8fb;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:12px;font-size:.9rem;color:var(--soft)}
  code{background:#eef3f9;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:5px;font-size:.85em}
  @media(max-width:900px){.grid{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}}
  @media(max-width:560px){.grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
</style>
  <div class="wrap">
    <h1>Caterlord — design refresh</h1>
    <p class="lede">Same real content and images in every option. <strong>A–C</strong> are solid, recognizable directions; <strong>D–F</strong> are more concept-led and brave. Pick one (or describe a mix) and I’ll build it into the site and lock it into a design system.</p>

    <div class="group">Directional — A · B · C</div>
    <div class="grid">
      <a class="card a" href="option-a-atelier.html"><div class="thumb">A</div><div class="b"><span class="tag">Editorial · light</span><h2>Atelier</h2><p>Warm cream, serif headlines, asymmetric magazine layout. Premium, confident.</p></div></a>
      <a class="card b" href="option-b-cobalt.html"><div class="thumb">B</div><div class="b"><span class="tag">Clean SaaS · light</span><h2>Cobalt</h2><p>White, grotesk type, bento grid. Trustworthy, modern, easy to scan.</p></div></a>
      <a class="card c" href="option-c-midnight.html"><div class="thumb">C</div><div class="b"><span class="tag">Atmospheric · dark</span><h2>Midnight</h2><p>Near-black, blue→teal glow, glass cards. High-tech, cutting-edge.</p></div></a>
    </div>

    <div class="group">Concept-led & brave — D · E · F</div>
    <div class="grid">
      <a class="card d" href="option-d-ticket.html"><div class="thumb">D</div><div class="b"><span class="tag">On-brand concept</span><h2>Order Ticket</h2><p>The whole page is a POS kitchen ticket — mono + slab, dashed edges, red stamp. Nobody else does this.</p></div></a>
      <a class="card e" href="option-e-brutalist.html"><div class="thumb">E <span>●</span></div><div class="b"><span class="tag">Brutalist · bold</span><h2>Grid</h2><p>Oversized condensed type, strict modular grid, hard shadows, electric blue. “We mean business.”</p></div></a>
      <a class="card f" href="option-f-hospitality.html"><div class="thumb">F</div><div class="b"><span class="tag">Hospitality · warm</span><h2>Hospitality</h2><p>Reframes the POS as a hospitality partner — full-bleed photography, terracotta + forest, elegant serif.</p></div></a>
    </div>

    <div class="note">Brand blue <code>#00B0FA</code> stays the anchor throughout (it’s the logo color). The creative directions may reprise it as a secondary accent while leading with a stronger palette.</div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
